Spacing,  formatting, and  presentation are  centrally important.  I want
those headers and headings, and  dividing lines. Your output should match
my output (all to STDOUT).

An issue you might  run into is how much space will  you have to allocate
(you want it universal for the display  of the entire table). For that, I
say  determine the  length  of the  maximum value  being  output (ie  the
bottom-most right value). That valueâ€™s length should then influence all
the other output in the table.

=====Verification=====
For  additional  help  in  attaining output  and  formatting  compliance,
I  have  included a  copy  of  my  implementation,  which abides  by  the
project specifications.  Please compare its  output against that  of your
implementation.

Run the provided "verify" program  with whatever combination of arguments
to obtain the output that your implementation needs to reproduce.

Do NOTE: the "verify" program, on error, will exit with a non-zero value,
but it  will NOT  necessarily be  the same non-zero  value you  have been
allocated.

Additional requirements
=======================
In your  finished, submitted product, no  line in the script  should span
longer  than 90  characters. This  includes  both script  logic and  your
comments.

  * script should be called "0x0"  and be located in  this 0x0/ directory
    of the EoCE.

  * if  there are any naming  manipulations needed on the  script, create
    them as symbolic links against the "0x0" script.

  * submit  with the rest  of the EoCE, by  running "make submit"  in the
    base "eoce" directory.

  * specific  output  to  STDOUT  vs STDERR  is  important,  as  is   the
    formatting of output in regards to justification and spacing.

The resultant  script MUST be well-organized,  easy-to-read, consistently
indented  visually  showing the  encapsulated  levels  of logic,  and  be
thoroughly commented to explain each significant step of the process.
